{"questionId":"22515105","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider one clockwise revolution of the sprinkler.</p>\n<p>At <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, the water crosses the edge of the path at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>At time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds, the water crosses the edge of the path at a movable point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> which is a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> metres south of point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>β</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>β</mi></math> are measured in radians.</p>\n<p>This information is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/aac310f1e137ae4b2a21c6cc8570350cdbce13ef.png\" width=\"423\" height=\"354\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22515105","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.11d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down an expression for α in terms of t.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}